Hi Everyone

Wij wonen op het vrachtschip De Flamingo gebouwd in 1930.  We bewonen het samen en regelmatig zijn Peter zijn 2 kinderen aan boord. We spenderen veel tijd om het schip mooi te houden. Sinds kort ligt het schip op een vaste ligplaats waar we vanaf het grote buiten terras  kunnen genieten van het prachtige weidse uitzicht op het pittoreske Durgerdam het IJvuur en natuurlijk het Markermeer. Ook springen we geregeld in het schone water!
Niet van origine een Amsterdammer maar kan niet meer zonder deze stad. Ik werk keihard voor en in het onderwijs. Ik ben gek op ruimtes inrichten en mooi maken met weinig middelen.

married love to travel love to sport

Hi all

The appartment is light cozy and feels very homey and is perfectly suited for 2. Regards 
Bauke and Leontien
My name is Inez I'm from Amsterdam and work as a psychologist.

Wittenberg is a monumental short stay building offering modern accommodation in Amsterdam's residential area. Carre Theater and the Dutch National Opera & Ballet are just 500 meters from the property. All other city highlights are easily accessible by pubic transport. All apartments are fully equipped including flat-screen TVs (Smart HD TV) dishwasher oven and microwave. Each has its own bathroom with free toiletries and a hairdryer. For your comfort towels bed linen and a weekly housekeeping are provided. Some apartments also feature a washing machine and there are public laundry rooms. The Hermitage Museum is just 650 meters away while Artis Zoo is only 400 meters from Wittenberg. The nearest airport is Schiphol Airport 12 km away or a 30-minute drive by car.

Hello
I am Henriette living in Amsterdam since 1983 on several places.
I was born in Eindhoven in the South of Holland and studied at the University of Nijmegen and Amsterdam political science and film-science.
Many years I worked as a film/video/performance programmer in theatres. 
Since 1990 I am working as a TV journalist and now for many years for a current affairs program. 
I love my work. And I really enjoy going to arthouse movies experimental cinema music and dance.  
Traveling and seeing other cultures makes me happy as well as meeting my family eating with friends and biking with my partner.
I already have a B&B since 1999.  I like it so much : it enriches my life meeting all kinds of different people.

about: Traveller.  Digital Nomad.

Hi my name is Merijn living in Amsterdam for 11 years. I really enjoy this vibrant city that surprises me again and again.
In 2014 I bought my own house and that's a joy. Because I are not at home all the time I thought about sharing my house with you the travellers. My crib is close to the city centre but in a quiet and green environment. My style of living is quite simple not too much clutter around the house. Just the things you need and some inspiring/funny decorations and lovely plants.
My hobbies: friends family music enjoying food and drinks to enjoy the small things. And of course travelling. I have been to several parts of the world also for longer periods of time. 
I speak English some Spanish Dutch and some German.
I would love to meet new people from around the world so be my guest!
Greetings
Merijn

Hi there hello I'm Mark.

A welcoming Dutch guy gay easygoing and with a broad interest.

Have been hosting via Airbnb for some time now and so far it has been an awesome experience. It's lovely to share this unique location and meet all kinds of super-nice people from across the globe.

A travel enthusiast currently making a stop in Amsterdam.
